He said he wanted to prove he was “worth something” so as not to disappoint everyone when they finally found out about his sexuality.
The two-time bronze Olympic medalist became a prominent LGBT activist and used his performance at this year’s Commonwealth Games in Australia to appeal to more countries to decriminalize homosexuality.
He said he decided to express himself because he felt happy to be able to live openly, without any implications, and thus wanted to give others “hope.”
