“Last year, the most important thing for me was to win a gold medal,” he said.
“And you know what? There are more important things than Olympic gold medals.
“My Olympic gold medal is Robbie.”
His son bears the same name as his father Robert, who died in 2011 at the age of 40 after being diagnosed with brain cancer.
Daley said his father did not accept that he was dying, and one of the last things he asked about was whether they already had tickets to the 2012 London Olympics — he wanted to be in the front row.
“I couldn’t tell him, ‘You won’t be with us to be in the front row, Dad,’” he said.
